title: BTS Jungkook- In This Together
body:
The one where Jungkook is your favorite Knight

I gasp as they bring him in, his feet barely lifting off the ground as he tries to keep up with the two other men who were holding him up. They bring him over to the bench and sit him down getting him to wince in pain holding his stomach. I quickly pick up a wash bucket and make my way over to them “Princess… We’ll get the nurse, don’t dirty your dress,” Namjoon tried stopping me, “The nurse will take too long, plus she’s very busy, I’m just as capable of taking care of wounds,” I replied setting the bucket down next to Jungkook. I started untying the strings of his armor looking at the other two “We’re in a very important war, I’m sure you two have other things to do than stand here,” I said getting them to nod and quickly rush off leaving the room. “I told you to be more careful,” I scolded looking at Jungkook while ripping his shirt open to reveal his perfectly toned body, a nice sized gash in his lower side, “Relax princess,” he managed to say through gritted teeth as I gently run my wet cloth over his injury trying to rid it of any disease.

His skin was hot, tot against his muscles, I couldn’t help but blush as my fingers run over his skin “I can wait for the nurse you know,” he teased getting me to shake my head. I took his chin in my hand and ran the cloth over his face to rid it of any blood and sweat that might have been left behind. “The question is why the princess gives me special treatment?” he asked as I let go of his chin, “The real question is how you survived this long when you’re so violently self-destructive,” I replied. He smirked “I’m reckless yes, but I’m also skilled,” he told me, I kneeled down between his legs, so I was eye level with his wound, winding the thread through the needle before sticking it through his skin. “Are you going to answer my question?” he asked through gritted teeth and I looked at him with a confused look “What question?” I asked before going back to sewing up his skin. “You… give me special treatment, I just wonder why,” he explained and I felt embarrassed my feelings were so openly visible.

“You’re my knight,” I told him simply, “You have many knights,” he countered as I tied up the string and cut it off looking up at him “But you’re the best one,” I replied softly getting up. I took care of his other wounds before helping him into a new clean shirt. Afterwards he leaned back a little, a lazy lock falling over his eyes “Sometimes it just doesn’t seem worth it you know?” he said stopping me from leaving “What?” I asked softly, “You wondered how I’ve survived this long when I’m so self-destructive and honestly I don’t know how… Everything. The war. The battles. Life. All of it doesn’t seem worth it,” he looked up at me his brown eyes locking with mine “But then I remember you,” he said getting up his face cringing in pain. I felt my breath catch in my throat “Jungkook-“ I managed to say his name but as his body neared mine, I seemed to have forgotten all the words in the dictionary.

“I know, I know. We come from different worlds. You’re a princess, loved and admired by all, with the softest hands and the gentlest touch. And I’m a knight who’s fought all his life, who’s hands are calloused and touch rough. You could never settle for someone like me,” he mumbled letting his gaze fall to the ground between us “There’s a better man out there that probably deserves you… And-and I don’t want to… but I love you.” He lifts his head to look at me “You’re everything to me princess, the beginning and the end. It’s why I keep fighting,” he explained. He smiled sadly reaching out his hand placing it on my cheek to wipe the tear off my cheek, “I didn’t mean to upset you,” he muttered. I leaned forward pressing my lips to his for a brief moment, before pulling back an inch to look into his dark eyes “Princess-“ “Kiss me Jungkook,” I demanded.

His hand on my cheek moved into my hair to hold the back of my head, his other arm coming around my waist pulling my body towards his own until we were chest to chest. My hands were resting on his chest and my nose was brushing against his, excitement filling my body from head to toe, I swear he could feel my heartbeat through my chest. He presses his pouted lips against mine, once, twice, as if testing to see if I was actually willing to kiss him back. Once I proved I reciprocated his mouth started attacking mine with hungry passion, and I kissed him back with the same vigor. We kissed like we were trying to swallow each other whole, mouths attacking each other, his tongue exploring my mouth claiming every part, hands sliding everywhere as if he was trying to imprint his touch into my skin, his fingers leaving traces in my hair, but I didn’t even care.

He pulled back slightly, and I leaned up on my toes to reconnect our lips getting him to smile into the kiss. “Princess,” he hummed placing his hand on my hip to force me back down on my palm of my feet, “Someone might come any second for me,” he said fixing my hair behind my ear. “So let them,” I replied innocently, but he shook his head no “I don’t want to get you in trouble,” he replied letting his forehead fall against mine. He closed his eyes as if to memorize the moment so whenever he closed his eyes this is all he would feel “You’ve done more than enough for me,” he whispered taking a deep breath. I wanted to tell him he hadn’t done enough for me, I wanted more of him, I wanted all of him, but I couldn’t find the words to express that. “I should go,” he said letting his eyes to look at me, he then gently pulled his hands away from me and took a step back letting my hands fall from his chest down to my sides. “I’m sure I’ll be back princess,” he replied giving me a bright smile before turning around slowly limping towards the door, but I couldn’t let him leave “how is it enough for you?” I asked taking a desperate step forward.

He stopped dead in his tracks and looked over his shoulder at me “Because, for a fraction of a second you were only mine,” he replied simply. I felt tears well in my eyes, “You weren’t someone’s daughter, you weren’t someone’s princess, you were mine, and no one else will ever get to feel that way,” he added, and he would forever be the only one to feel that way. “What if… what if it wasn’t enough for me?” I questioned wringing my hands together, he furrowed his eyebrows turning around to look at me “I don’t understand,” he replied. I crossed the room until I was back right in front of him “What if… I said I loved you too?” I asked him, a hurt look almost crossed his face “Don’t torment me,” he complained and I shook my head “I mean it Jungkook,” I told him reaching up to take his face between my palms “Why else would I treat you differently than the other knights? Why are you the one I ask to be on night duty when I can’t fall asleep? Why would I allow you to kiss me?” I whispered forcing him to look down at me.

“We’re from different worlds princess,” he whispered reaching up to place his hands over mine and pull them from his face, holding them between us “I’m not-“ “Don’t you finish that sentence Jeon Jungkook,” I cut him off sternly dropping his hands to wrap my arms around his neck “I’m in love with you, my strong, loyal, brave knight,” I whispered looking desperately into his eyes. “Princess…” he said breathlessly placing his hands on my waist “You’re the one I choose Jungkook and no one, not even my father can change my mind,” I told him seriously, getting him to look at me with his big doe eyes “I would leave this life of royalty and live on the streets as a peasant as long as I was with you,” I added. I leaned up pressing a few soft kisses to his lips, “Princess… I can’t ask that of you,” he mumbled, I shook my head “You’re not asking, it’s what I want,” I told him “Just promise me we’re in this together.” And he broke into a slight smile.

“We’re in this together.”

I felt my breath catch in my throat “Jungkook-“ I managed to say his name but as his body neared mine, I seemed to have forgotten all the words in the dictionary.

“I know, I know. We come from different worlds. You’re a princess, loved and admired by all, with the softest hands and the gentlest touch. And I’m a knight who’s fought all his life, who’s hands are calloused and touch rough. You could never settle for someone like me,” he mumbled letting his gaze fall to the ground between us “There’s a better man out there that probably deserves you… And-and I don’t want to… but I love you.” He lifts his head to look at me “You’re everything to me princess, the beginning and the end. It’s why I keep fighting,” he explained. He smiled sadly reaching out his hand placing it on my cheek to wipe the tear off my cheek, “I didn’t mean to upset you,” he muttered. I leaned forward pressing my lips to his for a brief moment, before pulling back an inch to look into his dark eyes “Princess-“ “Kiss me Jungkook,” I demanded.

His hand on my cheek moved into my hair to hold the back of my head, his other arm coming around my waist pulling my body towards his own until we were chest to chest. My hands were resting on his chest and my nose was brushing against his, excitement filling my body from head to toe, I swear he could feel my heartbeat through my chest. He presses his pouted lips against mine, once, twice, as if testing to see if I was actually willing to kiss him back. Once I proved I reciprocated his mouth started attacking mine with hungry passion, and I kissed him back with the same vigor. We kissed like we were trying to swallow each other whole, mouths attacking each other, his tongue exploring my mouth claiming every part, hands sliding everywhere as if he was trying to imprint his touch into my skin, his fingers leaving traces in my hair, but I didn’t even care.

He pulled back slightly, and I leaned up on my toes to reconnect our lips getting him to smile into the kiss. “Princess,” he hummed placing his hand on my hip to force me back down on my palm of my feet, “Someone might come any second for me,” he said fixing my hair behind my ear. “So let them,” I replied innocently, but he shook his head no “I don’t want to get you in trouble,” he replied letting his forehead fall against mine. He closed his eyes as if to memorize the moment so whenever he closed his eyes this is all he would feel “You’ve done more than enough for me,” he whispered taking a deep breath. I wanted to tell him he hadn’t done enough for me, I wanted more of him, I wanted all of him, but I couldn’t find the words to express that. “I should go,” he said letting his eyes to look at me, he then gently pulled his hands away from me and took a step back letting my hands fall from his chest down to my sides. “I’m sure I’ll be back princess,” he replied giving me a bright smile before turning around slowly limping towards the door, but I couldn’t let him leave “how is it enough for you?” I asked taking a desperate step forward.

He stopped dead in his tracks and looked over his shoulder at me “Because, for a fraction of a second you were only mine,” he replied simply. I felt tears well in my eyes, “You weren’t someone’s daughter, you weren’t someone’s princess, you were mine, and no one else will ever get to feel that way,” he added, and he would forever be the only one to feel that way. “What if… what if it wasn’t enough for me?” I questioned wringing my hands together, he furrowed his eyebrows turning around to look at me “I don’t understand,” he replied. I crossed the room until I was back right in front of him “What if… I said I loved you too?” I asked him, a hurt look almost crossed his face “Don’t torment me,” he complained and I shook my head “I mean it Jungkook,” I told him reaching up to take his face between my palms “Why else would I treat you differently than the other knights? Why are you the one I ask to be on night duty when I can’t fall asleep? Why would I allow you to kiss me?” I whispered forcing him to look down at me.

“We’re from different worlds princess,” he whispered reaching up to place his hands over mine and pull them from his face, holding them between us “I’m not-“ “Don’t you finish that sentence Jeon Jungkook,” I cut him off sternly dropping his hands to wrap my arms around his neck “I’m in love with you, my strong, loyal, brave knight,” I whispered looking desperately into his eyes. “Princess…” he said breathlessly placing his hands on my waist “You’re the one I choose Jungkook and no one, not even my father can change my mind,” I told him seriously, getting him to look at me with his big doe eyes “I would leave this life of royalty and live on the streets as a peasant as long as I was with you,” I added. I leaned up pressing a few soft kisses to his lips, “Princess… I can’t ask that of you,” he mumbled, I shook my head “You’re not asking, it’s what I want,” I told him “Just promise me we’re in this together.” And he broke into a slight smile.

“We’re in this together.”
